metadata.Subject:
Charles S. Phalen, Jr. is the Director of the National Background Investigations Bureau. In this
role, he reports to the OPM Director and leads a newly established entity within the U.S. Office
of Personnel Management, a government-wide service provider for background investigations.
He also partners with the Department of Defense, which is responsible for designing, building,
securing, and operating the NBIB information technology systems.
